<br>
Where would you suggest we hunt to equip our toons?  Our highest level is 6. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ellanon>Ellanon</A> at: 7/1/03 4:50 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gyreredbranch>Gyre Redbranch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/1/03 7:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4545.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hunting for Loot</span><hr size=1> The easiest way to equip a new character, or set of new characters, is to farm tradeskill items.  Spider silks and the like sell for decent plat in the bazaar, and you can put yourself in full ry'gorr or the like without a great deal of effort.<br>
<br>
Alternately, find someplace with a lot of wisps and kill those.  The greater lightstones sell for a very tidy sum (10p or so, if memory serves) to the gypsies in N Karana.  Then head to the bazaar.<br>
<br>
The bazaar has made self-twinking really, really easy.<br>
